{"type":"message","id":"830c068d","parentId":"f39cdfd8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T04:15:25.866Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the root cause clearly. Two intertwined problems:\n\n1. **Corrupted `creds.json`** — every reconnect cycle triggers `\"restored corrupted WhatsApp creds.json from backup\"`. The credentials file is getting corrupted on each connection, and the backup it restores from is *also* bad (or becomes bad again immediately).\n\n2. **Status 499 loop** — WhatsApp's web socket connects, lasts ~60 seconds, then drops with status 499 (client closed request). The corrupted creds mean it can't maintain a valid session.\n\nLet me check the creds file:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_FTCYApT24IqP69jGs36AkO","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/default/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"===\"; file /home/openclaw/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/default/creds.json 2>/dev/null; echo \"===\"; wc -c /home/openclaw/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/default/creds.json 2>/dev/null; echo \"===\"; ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/default/*.bak* 2>/dev/null || echo \"no backup files\"","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_Gxtrdw4h2b0kamO17S0sd1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check how long this flapping has been going on\ngrep \"restored corrupted WhatsApp creds.json\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-01.log 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"===\"; grep \"restored corrupted WhatsApp creds.json\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-01.log 2>/dev/null | wc -l; echo \"total occurrences today\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":503,"cacheRead":28014,"cacheWrite":11726,"totalTokens":40244,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.012575000000000001,"cacheRead":0.014006999999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0732875,"total":0.0998745}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp"