{"type":"message","id":"68944448","parentId":"499b8ccb","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:15:54.590Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_6MRazuTvImlKUJYzylunUN","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-01 — Daily Notes\n\n## WhatsApp Gateway Flapping (04:14 UTC)\n- **Status:** WhatsApp gateway in 60-second disconnect/reconnect loop since ~00:34 UTC\n- **Root cause:** `creds.json` being flagged as corrupted every reconnect cycle → backup restore → reconnect → repeat\n- **Details:** 59 \"restored corrupted creds.json\" occurrences today. Status 499 (client-closed) every ~60s\n- **Investigation:** creds.json is actually valid JSON with correct fields (me.id, registrationId, etc.) — may be a file-locking/write-race issue\n- **Impact:** WhatsApp messages may work intermittently (brief connected windows), but loop wastes resources\n- **Gateway:** Running as openclaw-gateway (PID 1067470), child of openclaw supervisor (PID 1067463), NOT in PM2\n- **Action needed:** Lucy should try `openclaw gateway restart` or kill+restart the supervisor process when awake\n- **Risk:** Low — it's a nuisance loop, not data loss. Telegram still works fine.\n- **Note:** The gateway also reports whatsapp plugin as \"not found\" (stale config entry) — may need cleanup\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775031354586}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a5fa043","parentId":"68944448","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:16:15.651Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_bbwyXn4YZ66AC5iJLKifsh","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-01.md","content":"# 2026-04-01 — Daily Notes\n\n## WhatsApp Gateway Flapping (04:14 UTC)\n- **Status:** WhatsApp gateway in 60-second disconnect/reconnect loop since ~00:34 UTC\n- **Root cause:** `creds.json` being flagged as corrupted every reconnect cycle → backup restore → reconnect → repeat\n- **Details:** 59 \"restored corrupted creds.json\" occurrences today. Status 499 (client-closed) every ~60s\n- **Investigation:** creds.json is actually valid JSON with correct fields (me.id, registrationId, etc.) — may be a file-locking/write-race issue\n- **Impact:** WhatsApp messages may work intermittently (brief connected windows), but loop wastes resources\n- **Gateway:** Running as openclaw-gateway (PID 1067470), child of openclaw supervisor (PID 1067463), NOT in PM2\n- **Action needed:** Lucy should try `openclaw gateway restart` or kill+restart the supervisor process when awake\n- **Risk:** Low — it's a nuisance loop, not data loss. Telegram still works fine.\n- **Note:** The gateway also reports whatsapp plugin as \"not found\" (stale config entry) — may need cleanup\n\n## Sentra Brochure Copywriting Session (05:00-08:15 UTC)\n- **Context:** Lucy working on Sentra Technology product catalog/brosur in Canva\n- **My role:** Writing product descriptions, taglines, bullet points for each product page\n- **Products covered:**\n  1. **FMS (Fleet Management System)** — Dashboard, GPS tracking, ritase, BBM, CCTV, geofence, face recognition. Checked fms.sentratechnology.com demo vs brochure claims. 2/6 features fully present, 3 partial, 1 missing (CAN-Bus health).\n  2. **Custom Landing Page / Web App / Mobile App** — Combined into 1 package with 12 bullets + garansi & support 2 tahun\n  3. **HRIS** — Absensi GPS, face recognition, payroll, cuti, shift management\n  4. **Safety Attribute Detection (AI CCTV)** — APD detection (helm, safety belt, sepatu, rompi) + Starlink + Solar Panel\n  5. **Smart Lock System** — PIN, kartu, fingerprint, app access + monitoring\n  6. **SentrAI (On-Premise AI Server)** — 50 juta, server + AI + enkripsi\n  7. **Starlink Packages** (6 variants) — Home Starter, Home Basic, Home Ultra, Enterprise, Solar Coverage, Solar Coverage Max. Fixed all taglines (were all identical \"Cocok untuk penggunaan ringan & mobile\")\n  8. **Telematics (Teltonika)** — CAN-Bus, multi-sensor, dual-SIM, industrial grade, GPS, BBM monitoring, ADAS\n- **Key issue:** Space constraints in Canva — text kept overlapping. Had to shorten bullets multiple times.\n- **Format shift:** Lucy moved from multi-product-per-page to 1-product-per-page layout. Much cleaner.\n- **FMS page finalized** with 10 bullets + descriptive paragraph, price Rp 518 juta.\n- **Lucy asked if I can edit Canva directly** — told him it's not practical (UI-heavy), recommended sticking with copy-paste workflow.\n- **Sentra context:** This is Lucy's IT company (he's PM), separate from DataFlow. Products are for B2B sales in Kaltim.\n"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":953,"cacheRead":34168,"cacheWrite":383,"totalTokens":35505,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.023825000000000002,"cacheRead":0.017084,"cacheWrite":0.00239375,"total":0.043307750000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775031354591}}
