{"type":"message","id":"fe26ce1d","parentId":"4677bc5d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:19:59.438Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_6E8O0gaYvX4wXmHD5XiecS","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## D&D 5e SRD API\nURL: https://5e-bits.github.io/docs/\nD&D 5e SRD API. REST + GraphQL API for the 5e SRD database. Get Started Try the API. Community. Discord. Contribute. API Source · Docs Source\n\n## 5e-bits/5e-srd-api: REST API to access D&D 5th Edition SRD database\nURL: https://github.com/5e-bits/5e-srd-api\nREST API to access D&D 5th Edition SRD database. Contribute to 5e-bits/5e-srd-api development by creating an account on GitHub.\n\n## GitHub - 5e-bits/5e-database: Database for the D&D 5th Edition API\nURL: https://github.com/5e-bits/5e-database\nDatabase for the D&D 5th Edition API. Contribute to 5e-bits/5e-database development by creating an account on GitHub.\n\n## 5e-database download | SourceForge.net\nURL: https://sourceforge.net/projects/fivee-database.mirror/\nDownload 5e-database for free. Database for the D&D 5th Edition API. Just a simple API for things within the Official 5th Edition SRD and is easily\n\n## GraphQL Fundamentals | D&D 5e SRD API - GitHub Pages\nURL: https://5e-bits.github.io/docs/tutorials/beginner/graphql\nGraphQL is a powerful and flexible way to fetch data from the D&D 5e SRD API. In this tutorial, we will learn how to build and try out a range of GraphQL"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1050,"aggregated":"## D&D 5e SRD API\nURL: https://5e-bits.github.io/docs/\nD&D 5e SRD API. REST + GraphQL API for the 5e SRD database. Get Started Try the API. Community. Discord. Contribute. API Source · Docs Source\n\n## 5e-bits/5e-srd-api: REST API to access D&D 5th Edition SRD database\nURL: https://github.com/5e-bits/5e-srd-api\nREST API to access D&D 5th Edition SRD database. Contribute to 5e-bits/5e-srd-api development by creating an account on GitHub.\n\n## GitHub - 5e-bits/5e-database: Database for the D&D 5th Edition API\nURL: https://github.com/5e-bits/5e-database\nDatabase for the D&D 5th Edition API. Contribute to 5e-bits/5e-database development by creating an account on GitHub.\n\n## 5e-database download | SourceForge.net\nURL: https://sourceforge.net/projects/fivee-database.mirror/\nDownload 5e-database for free. Database for the D&D 5th Edition API. Just a simple API for things within the Official 5th Edition SRD and is easily\n\n## GraphQL Fundamentals | D&D 5e SRD API - GitHub Pages\nURL: https://5e-bits.github.io/docs/tutorials/beginner/graphql\nGraphQL is a powerful and flexible way to fetch data from the D&D 5e SRD API. In this tutorial, we will learn how to build and try out a range of GraphQL","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775056799428}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff88999d","parentId":"fe26ce1d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:20:10.957Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ada free API dan database buat D&D 5e SRD. Gw punya 2 pendekatan:\n\n**Approach 1 — Integrate 5e SRD API (recommended)**\nPake `https://www.dnd5eapi.co` — free REST API, no auth needed. Udah punya:\n- Semua spells, monsters, classes, races, equipment, feats\n- Searchable, filterable\n- JSON format — gampang integrate ke web kita\n\n**Approach 2 — Mirror 5e.tools**\nDownload source data-nya (mereka open source di GitHub), host di server kita. Lebih lengkap tapi *jauh* lebih berat.\n\nGw rekomendasiin **Approach 1** — tambahin tab \"Compendium\" di DnD app kita yang connect ke 5e SRD API. Include:\n- **Spells browser** — search, filter by class/level/school\n- **Monsters/Bestiary** — search, filter by CR/type\n- **Items & Equipment** — weapons, armor, magic items\n- **Classes & Races** — full descriptions & features\n- **AI Character Generator** — pake data dari API buat auto-generate characters\n\nIni lumayan besar — mau gw mulai sekarang atau lo mau gw prioritasin yang mana dulu (compendium browser atau AI character generator)?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":343,"cacheRead":112542,"cacheWrite":518,"totalTokens":113404,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.008575000000000001,"cacheRead":0.056270999999999995,"cacheWrite":0.0032375000000000004,"total":0.0680885}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775056799442}}
