{"type":"message","id":"233f960a","parentId":"a1bc987a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:22:09.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOke, gw mulai. Ini project lumayan besar jadi gw spawn subagent biar bisa kerja paralel tanpa block chat kita."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_UmPiejXVq2XFZnoMEryiLw","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are working on a D&D 2024 web app at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/\n\n## Task: Add a \"Compendium\" tab with full D&D 5e SRD data\n\n### Data Source\nSRD JSON data is already cloned at /tmp/5e-database/src/ (both 2014/ and 2024/ folders).\n\n1. Copy the JSON files to /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/srd/ (both 2014 and 2024)\n2. Add backend API endpoints to serve the data\n3. Add a \"Compendium\" tab in the frontend\n\n### Backend (server.js at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/backend/server.js)\n- Add GET endpoints: /api/srd/spells, /api/srd/monsters, /api/srd/classes, /api/srd/races, /api/srd/equipment, /api/srd/magic-items, /api/srd/feats, /api/srd/conditions, /api/srd/backgrounds, /api/srd/skills\n- Each endpoint should support ?search=keyword query param for filtering\n- Serve both 2014 and 2024 data (default to 2024, ?edition=2014 for old)\n- Load JSON files once at startup into memory for fast access\n\n### Frontend (app.js at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/app.js, index.html at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/index.html, styles.css at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css)\nThe app uses a tab-based SPA architecture. Look at how existing tabs work (Character, Battle Map, etc.) and follow the same pattern.\n\nAdd a \"Compendium\" tab (📚 icon) with these sections:\n- **Spells** — searchable list with filters: class, level (0-9), school. Click to expand full details\n- **Monsters/Bestiary** — searchable with CR filter, type filter. Show stats block on click\n- **Classes** — list all classes with features, subclasses\n- **Races/Species** — traits, ability bonuses\n- **Equipment** — weapons, armor, adventuring gear, costs\n- **Magic Items** — rarity filter, description\n- **Feats** — prerequisites, description\n- **Conditions** — name + description\n\nUI Style: Match the existing dark fantasy theme (dark backgrounds, gold/amber accents). The app uses CSS variables extensively - check styles.css.\n\nEach section should have:\n- Search bar at top\n- Filter dropdowns where applicable\n- Card-based results grid\n- Click to expand details in a modal or side panel\n\n### Important\n- Don't break existing functionality\n- Follow the same code patterns used in the existing codebase\n- Add the Compendium nav button in the sidebar alongside existing tabs\n- After changes, restart with: pm2 restart dnd-app\n- Test that the app loads without errors: pm2 logs dnd-app --lines 10 --nostream\n\n### Also hook into AI Character Generator\nWhen the AI generates a character, it should pull real spell names, equipment names, etc. from the SRD data instead of making them up. Update the character creation flow to reference the compendium data.","mode":"run","label":"dnd-compendium","runTimeoutSeconds":600}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":929,"cacheRead":115481,"cacheWrite":371,"totalTokens":116784,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.023225000000000003,"cacheRead":0.0577405,"cacheWrite":0.00231875,"total":0.08329925}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775056903180}}
