{"type":"message","id":"c499c25e","parentId":"0e5fe63f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T18:04:09.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Jackpot — 106MB of pure D&D data. Semua sourcebook, semua spells, semua monsters. Sekarang gw extract yang penting dan integrate ke app kita."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_1u3E24EdbJF3og2kd9J52X","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check how many spells, monsters, classes total\necho \"=== SPELLS ===\"\nfor f in /tmp/5etools-src/data/spells/spells-*.json; do\n  count=$(python3 -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('$f')); print(len(d.get('spell',[])))\" 2>/dev/null)\n  echo \"$(basename $f): $count\"\ndone | sort -t: -k2 -rn | head -10\n\necho -e \"\\n=== MONSTERS ===\"\ntotal=0\nfor f in /tmp/5etools-src/data/bestiary/bestiary-*.json; do\n  count=$(python3 -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('$f')); print(len(d.get('monster',[])))\" 2>/dev/null)\n  total=$((total + count))\ndone\necho \"Total monsters: $total\"\n\necho -e \"\\n=== CLASSES ===\"\nls /tmp/5etools-src/data/class/class-*.json | wc -l","timeout":30}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":378,"cacheRead":128917,"cacheWrite":536,"totalTokens":129832,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.00945,"cacheRead":0.0644585,"cacheWrite":0.00335,"total":0.07726350000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775066638491}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ee59e2c","parentId":"c499c25e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T18:04:16.018Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_1u3E24EdbJF3og2kd9J52X","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== SPELLS ===\nspells-xphb.json: 391\nspells-phb.json: 361\nspells-xge.json: 95\nspells-tce.json: 21\nspells-frhof.json: 19\nspells-egw.json: 15\nspells-ftd.json: 7\nspells-ai.json: 7\nspells-scc.json: 5\nspells-llk.json: 3\n\n=== MONSTERS ===\nTotal monsters: 4454\n\n=== CLASSES ===\n15"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6842,"aggregated":"=== SPELLS ===\nspells-xphb.json: 391\nspells-phb.json: 361\nspells-xge.json: 95\nspells-tce.json: 21\nspells-frhof.json: 19\nspells-egw.json: 15\nspells-ftd.json: 7\nspells-ai.json: 7\nspells-scc.json: 5\nspells-llk.json: 3\n\n=== MONSTERS ===\nTotal monsters: 4454\n\n=== CLASSES ===\n15","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775066656004}}
{"type":"message","id":"3afceefb","parentId":"2ee59e2c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T18:04:49.034Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**4454 monsters, 900+ spells, 15 classes** — vs onze huidige 334 monsters en 319 spells. Massive upgrade."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_czekYErXjmjGI0YdaN1qrl","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"dnd-content-upgrade","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"You are working on a D&D web app at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/\n\n## Task: Upgrade Compendium with FULL 5e.tools data (900+ spells, 4400+ monsters, 15 classes, all items)\n\n### Data Source\nFull 5etools data is at /tmp/5etools-src/data/ (106MB). This contains ALL sourcebooks.\n\n### Step 1: Merge & Process Data\nCreate a script at /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/build-srd.js that:\n\n1. Reads ALL spell files from /tmp/5etools-src/data/spells/spells-*.json, merges into one array\n2. Reads ALL bestiary files from /tmp/5etools-src/data/bestiary/bestiary-*.json, merges into one array  \n3. Reads ALL class files from /tmp/5etools-src/data/class/class-*.json\n4. Reads items.json, magicitems.json (or similar) \n5. Reads feats.json, backgrounds.json, conditionsdiseases.json, races.json (or fluff-races.json)\n6. Outputs merged JSON files to /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/5etools/ as:\n   - all-spells.json\n   - all-monsters.json  \n   - all-classes.json\n   - all-items.json (equipment + magic items)\n   - all-feats.json\n   - all-conditions.json\n   - all-races.json\n   - all-backgrounds.json\n\nRun the script after creating it.\n\n### Step 2: Update Backend (/home/openclaw/dnd-app/backend/server.js)\n\nReplace the current SRD data loading with the new 5etools data:\n- Load the merged JSON files at startup\n- Update all /api/srd/* endpoints to serve the new data\n- Add proper filtering: \n  - Spells: filter by name, level, school, class, source book\n  - Monsters: filter by name, CR, type, source\n  - Classes: include all subclasses and features per level\n  - Items: filter by type, rarity\n- Add pagination support: ?page=1&limit=50 (default 50 per page)\n- Keep the existing endpoint structure, just more data\n\n### Step 3: Update Frontend (/home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/app.js)\n\nThe Compendium tab already exists with categories, search, and filters. Upgrade it:\n\n**Spells detail view** — when clicking a spell, show:\n- Name, level, school, casting time, range, components (V/S/M with material details)\n- Duration, concentration indicator\n- Full description text (properly formatted with paragraphs)\n- At Higher Levels section\n- Class list that can use it\n- Source book\n\n**Monster detail view** — show full stat block:\n- Name, size, type, alignment\n- AC, HP (hit dice), Speed\n- All 6 ability scores with modifiers\n- Saving throws, skills, damage immunities/resistances/vulnerabilities\n- Senses, languages, CR (with XP)\n- Traits, Actions, Legendary Actions, Lair Actions\n- Properly formatted like a D&D stat block (the classic tan-colored box style)\n\n**Class detail view:**\n- Class description, hit dice, proficiencies\n- Features by level (expandable/collapsible)\n- Subclass list with features\n- Spell list for spellcasters\n\n**Item detail view:**\n- Name, type, weight, cost\n- Description, properties\n- For magic items: rarity, attunement, full description\n\n**Feat detail:**\n- Prerequisites\n- Full description with bullet points\n\n**Also update filters:**\n- Spells: add \"Source Book\" filter dropdown\n- Monsters: add \"Source Book\" filter, CR range slider\n- Items: add rarity filter (Common, Uncommon, Rare, Very Rare, Legendary, Artifact)\n\n### Step 4: Performance\nWith 4400+ monsters, we need:\n- Virtual scrolling or \"Load More\" button (show 50 at a time)\n- Debounced search (300ms delay)\n- Server-side filtering (don't send all 4400 monsters to client at once)\n\n### Important\n- DON'T break existing functionality (character sheet, battle map, etc.)\n- Match existing dark fantasy UI theme\n- The app already has CSS variables and styles - use them\n- After ALL changes: pm2 restart dnd-app\n- Verify no errors: pm2 logs dnd-app --lines 10 --nostream\n- The 5etools data format has entries like: spell.entries (array of strings/objects for description), monster.ac (array), monster.hp (object with formula), etc. Handle these properly.\n- For monster stat blocks, create a dedicated CSS class that looks like the classic D&D stat block (tan parchment background, red divider lines, proper typography)"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":1335,"cacheRead":129453,"cacheWrite":530,"totalTokens":131319,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.033375,"cacheRead":0.06472649999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0033125000000000003,"total":0.10141899999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775066656024}}
